<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Opensource Sunday – Communications</title><link>https://opensourcesunday.com/confirmation/communications/</link><description>Recent content in Communications on Opensource Sunday</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://opensourcesunday.com/confirmation/communications/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Invites</title><link>https://opensourcesunday.com/confirmation/communications/invites/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://opensourcesunday.com/confirmation/communications/invites/</guid><description>
&lt;a
class=" not-prose hx:inline-flex hx:items-center hx:rounded-full hx:gap-2 hx:px-3 hx:py-1 hx:text-xs hx:text-gray-600 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:bg-gray-100 hx:dark:bg-neutral-800 hx:border-gray-200 hx:dark:border-neutral-800 hx:border hx:hover:border-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50 hx:dark:hover:border-gray-600 hx:transition-all hx:ease-in hx:duration-200"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-2 hx:h-2 hx:rounded-full hx:bg-yellow-400"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;span&gt;Draft · still being polished&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recruiting next year&amp;rsquo;s class.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These go out in the spring — usually to the rising 9th-grade confirmation list (current 8th-graders). We send both: an email invite for families who are already in the digital loop, and a physical mailing for families who aren&amp;rsquo;t. Both should arrive the same week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;The mailing includes the same content as the email, but with a little more warmth and a printed calendar preview on the back. Parents save paper; kids don&amp;rsquo;t read email.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Parent Emails</title><link>https://opensourcesunday.com/confirmation/communications/parent-emails/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://opensourcesunday.com/confirmation/communications/parent-emails/</guid><description>
&lt;a
class=" not-prose hx:inline-flex hx:items-center hx:rounded-full hx:gap-2 hx:px-3 hx:py-1 hx:text-xs hx:text-gray-600 hx:dark:text-gray-400 hx:bg-gray-100 hx:dark:bg-neutral-800 hx:border-gray-200 hx:dark:border-neutral-800 hx:border hx:hover:border-gray-400 hx:dark:hover:text-gray-50 hx:dark:hover:border-gray-600 hx:transition-all hx:ease-in hx:duration-200"
&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-2 hx:h-2 hx:rounded-full hx:bg-yellow-400"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;span&gt;Draft · still being polished&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The season-long parent email series.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One email per session, sent the week before or after. These translate what we taught into a language parents can bring to the dinner table — &lt;em&gt;so what did you actually learn about sin last week?&lt;/em&gt; — and flag the practical stuff (dates, drop-offs, mentor expectations).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Cadence&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="cadence"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#cadence" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Per-session emails&lt;/strong&gt; (12 total, matching the twelve topics)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event emails&lt;/strong&gt; (parent class, dessert, Confirmation Sunday)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seasonal touchpoints&lt;/strong&gt; (post-fall-retreat, end-of-year)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:overflow-x-auto hx:mt-6 hx:flex hx:rounded-lg hx:border hx:py-2 hx:ltr:pr-4 hx:rtl:pl-4 hx:contrast-more:border-current hx:contrast-more:dark:border-current hx:border-blue-200 hx:bg-blue-100 hx:text-blue-900 hx:dark:border-blue-200/30 hx:dark:bg-blue-900/30 hx:dark:text-blue-200"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:ltr:pl-3 hx:ltr:pr-2 hx:rtl:pr-3 hx:rtl:pl-2"&gt;&lt;svg height=1.2em class="hx:inline-block hx:align-middle" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:w-full hx:min-w-0 hx:leading-7"&gt;
&lt;div class="hx:mt-6 hx:leading-7 hx:first:mt-0"&gt;These are templates. Keep the voice, swap the specifics. The value of the series is the &lt;em&gt;rhythm&lt;/em&gt; — parents know something&amp;rsquo;s landing in their inbox every couple of weeks, so they lean in instead of tuning out.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>